<section class="case_study_content asha">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="large-8 large-centered columns">
      <h2>A new way to get attention, without a ton of extra work</h2>
      <p>
        Janet McNichol, Director of Human Resources at ASHA, needed to find new ways to capture the attention of busy employees. Communications were already being posted to the intranet, Facebook, her blog 
        <a href="http://www.insideworkplacewellness.com/" target="_new">Inside Workplace Wellness</a>, and sent in weekly emails. Janet wanted a system that incorporated new technologies like mobile and gamification, but she simply didn’t have the time to take on a lot of new work.
      </p>

      <h2>Making content creation easy</h2>
      <p>Today, over 89% of employees have activated their accounts on the ASHA Board. Janet creates 4 to 6 posts each week about diverse topics, from introducing new hires to promoting wellness challenges. Janet sends an automatically generated email with the new posts once a week to all employees, prompting everyone to scan “what’s new” and earn points for engaging toward a prize like a Kindle Paperwhite.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

