      </div></div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="large-8 large-centered columns">
      <h2>Building a community of engagement</h2>
      <p>After the ASHA Board’s launch, Janet was approached by a number of colleagues who also wanted to post content, like key points from staff meetings for people that didn’t have a chance to attend. And, employees started encouraging their colleagues to participate. Over a third of participants were recruited to the ASHA Board by another colleague and 70% have made at least one connection with a colleague.</p>

      <h2>Metrics to support any objective</h2>
      <p>One of the key uses of the ASHA Board has been to promote open positions. Participants earn points each time they share a job post on their Facebook, Twitter or LinkedIn page. Using the ASHA Board’s analytics, Janet was able to show that in the first 8 weeks, 13 jobs were shared 289 times by over 70 people on their personal social networks, reaching an estimated 10,000 people.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


